def: An armor of bony plates, somewhat resembling a cuirass.
To comprise in, or reduce to, a summary; to present briefly.Chambers.
The state of being gradual; gradualness. [R.] Sir T. Browne.

Eating or feeding on flesh. The term is applied: (a) to animalswhich naturally seek flesh for food, as the tiger, dog, etc.; (b) toplants which are supposed to absorb animal food; (c) to substanceswhich destroy animal tissue, as caustics.
The note next above the keynote; the second of the scale.Busby.
The setting of one above another; preference. [R.] Jer. Taylor.
In a total manner; wholly; entirely.
